2 HOUSE BILL 1348
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Family Law
4 5–701.
5 (a) Except as otherwise provided in § 5–705.1 of this subtitle, in this subtitle the
6 following words have the meanings indicated.
7 (b) (1) “Abuse” means:
8 (ii) sexual abuse of a child, whether physical injuries are sustained
9 or not; or
10 (iii) labor trafficking of a child by any individual.
11 (m) “Labor trafficking” means knowingly:
12 (1) taking, placing, harboring, persuading, inducing, or enticing a child by
13 force, fraud, or coercion to provide services or labor; or
14 (2) receiving a benefit or thing of value from the provision of services or
15 labor by a child that was induced by force, fraud, or coercion.
16 (x) “Sex trafficking” means the recruitment, harboring, transportation, provision,
17 obtaining, patronizing, or soliciting of a child for the purpose of a commercial sex act.
18 (y) “Sexual abuse” means any act that involves:
19 (2) sex trafficking of a child by any individual.
20 5–704.
21 (a) (1) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, including any law on
22 privileged communications, each health practitioner, police officer, educator, or human
23 service worker, acting in a professional capacity in this State who has reason to believe that
24 a child has been subjected to abuse or neglect:
25 [(1)] (I) shall notify the local department or the appropriate law
26 enforcement agency; [and]
27 [(2)] (II) if acting as a staff member of a hospital, public health agency,
28 child care institution, juvenile detention center, school, or similar institution, shall
29 immediately notify and give all information required by this section to the head of the
30 institution or the designee of the head; AND

HOUSE BILL 1348 3
1 (III) MAY NOTIFY A REGIONAL NAVIGATOR AS DEFINED IN §
2 5–704.4 OF THIS SUBTITLE OF SUSPECTED SEX TRAFFICKING OR LABOR
3 TRAFFICKING IF, IN THE PROFESSIONAL JUDGMENT OF THE REPORTER,
4 NOTIFICATION IS NECESSARY TO PREVENT SERIOUS HARM TO THE CHILD OR OTHER
5 CHILDREN.
6 (2) AN INDIVIDUAL AUTHORIZED TO NOTIFY A REGIONAL NAVIGATOR
7 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(III) OF THIS SUBSECTION MAY NOTIFY THE REGIONAL
8 NAVIGATOR:
9 (I) WITHOUT THE CONSENT OF THE CHILD; AND
10 (II) OVER THE EXPRESS OBJECTION OF THE CHILD.
11 Article – Criminal Law
12 3–1104.
13 (A) A STATE’S ATTORNEY OR THE ATTORNEY GENERAL MAY INVESTIGATE
14 AND PROSECUTE A VIOLATION OF THIS SUBTITLE OR A VIOLATION OF ANY CRIME
15 BASED ON THE ACT ESTABLISHING A VIOLATION OF THIS SUBTITLE.
16 (B) IF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL EXERCISES AUTHORITY UNDER
17 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION, THE ATTORNEY GENERAL HAS ALL THE POWERS
18 AND DUTIES OF A STATE’S ATTORNEY TO INVESTIGATE AND PROSECUTE THE
19 VIOLATION.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
21 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
